---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy — Cowaty Digital Agency"
  description="Cowaty's Cookie Policy. How we use cookies on the Cowaty website and how to control your cookie preferences."
  canonicalPath="/cookie-policy"
  schemaType="WebPage"
>
  <section class="page-hero" aria-labelledby="cookie-hero-heading">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="section-label">Legal</p>
      <h1 id="cookie-hero-heading">Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p>How we use cookies on the Cowaty website and your options.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section style="padding-top: 4rem; padding-bottom: 6rem;">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="legal-content">
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: 19 April 2025</p>

        <p>
          This Cookie Policy explains how Cowaty ("we", "us", "our") uses cookies and similar
          tracking technologies on cowaty.com. It should be read alongside our
          <a href="/privacy-policy">Privacy Policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
        <p>
          Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They allow
          the website to recognise your device and remember information about your visit, such as
          your preferences or actions.
        </p>
        <p>
          Similar technologies include web beacons, pixel tags, and local storage. References to
          "cookies" in this policy include all such technologies unless stated otherwise.
        </p>

        <h2>2. How We Use Cookies</h2>

        <h3>Strictly Necessary Cookies</h3>
        <p>
          These cookies are essential for the website to function. They do not collect personal
          data and cannot be disabled. They include cookies set by our hosting provider for
          security and performance purposes.
        </p>

        <h3>Analytics Cookies (Optional)</h3>
        <p>
          We plan to use analytics cookies (such as Google Analytics) to understand how visitors
          use our site — which pages are most visited, how long people stay, and where they come
          from. These cookies will only be set if you consent. No analytics cookies are currently
          active on this site.
        </p>

        <h3>Marketing and Advertising Cookies (Optional)</h3>
        <p>
          If we run paid advertising campaigns that use retargeting (for example, Google Ads or
          Meta Ads remarketing), those platforms may set cookies to measure the effectiveness
          of our ads. These will only be deployed with your consent and will be disclosed when
          active.
        </p>

        <h2>3. Cookie Consent</h2>
        <p>
          In accordance with the UK Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations (PECR) and
          UK GDPR, we will seek your consent before setting any non-essential cookies. Strictly
          necessary cookies do not require consent as they are essential to deliver the service
          you have requested.
        </p>
        <p>
          You can withdraw or modify your consent at any time by clearing your browser cookies
          and revisiting the site, or by adjusting your browser settings as described below.
        </p>

        <h2>4. Managing Cookies via Your Browser</h2>
        <p>
          Most browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can typically:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>View and delete cookies already stored on your device.</li>
          <li>Block all cookies from being set.</li>
          <li>Block third-party cookies only.</li>
          <li>Allow cookies from specific websites.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          Please note that blocking certain cookies may affect the functionality of this website
          and other sites you visit. For instructions on managing cookies in your browser, refer to
          your browser's help documentation.
        </p>

        <h2>5. Third-Party Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          Some content on our website may be served by third parties. These third parties may
          set their own cookies subject to their own privacy and cookie policies. We have no
          control over these cookies. Third-party services currently in use or planned:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Analytics</strong> — analytics (consent required, not yet active)</li>
          <li><strong>Cloudflare</strong> — hosting, security, and performance (strictly necessary)</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>6. Do Not Track</h2>
        <p>
          Some browsers include a "Do Not Track" (DNT) feature that signals to websites that you
          do not wish to be tracked. There is currently no universal standard for interpreting DNT
          signals. We will honour DNT signals to the extent technically practicable as part of
          our broader respect for user privacy preferences.
        </p>

        <h2>7. Changes to This Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this Cookie Policy as our use of cookies changes or to reflect regulatory
          requirements. The current version will always be available at
          <a href="https://cowaty.com/cookie-policy">cowaty.com/cookie-policy</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>8. Contact</h2>
        <p>
          For questions about our use of cookies, contact us at
          <a href="mailto:hello@cowaty.com">hello@cowaty.com</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
